    public class AgentShardGeneral
extends AgentShardCore
    The class extends AgentShardCore and offers additional functionality for AgentShard implementations, especially in working together with other (known types of) shards.
    Author:
    Andrei Olaru

      • getMessagingShard

        protected MessagingShard getMessagingShard()
        Retrieves the agent's messaging shard. If a value is returned, it is usable (it implements MessagingShard). If no usable instance was found, an exception is thrown.
        Returns:
        an instance of MessagingShard.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - - if there is no messaging shard or it does not implement MessagingShard.

      • sendMessage

        protected boolean sendMessage​(java.lang.String content,
                              java.lang.String sourceInternalEndpoint,
                              java.lang.String targetAgent,
                              java.lang.String... targetPathElements)
        Uses the MessagingShard to send a message.
        Parameters:
        content - - the content of the message.
        sourceInternalEndpoint - - the source endpoint of the message (as an internal endpoint, to which the address of the agent will be added).
        targetAgent - - the name of the target agent.
        targetPathElements - - internal elements in the target path.
        Returns:
        true if the message has been successfully sent (as reported by the MessagingShard.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if no usable MessagingShard has been found.
